.TH AXT-GITCTX 1
.SH NAME
axt-gitctx \- emit bounded local Git context
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B axt-gitctx
[\fIROOT\fR] [--json|--agent] [--commits \fIN\fR] [--inline-diff-max-bytes \fIBYTES\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B axt-gitctx
returns repository root, branch, upstream, ahead/behind counts, dirty state,
changed files, diff stats, recent commits, and small inline diffs in one
bounded local call.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --commits N
Recent commits to include. Default 5.
.TP
.B --inline-diff-max-bytes BYTES
Maximum bytes for each inline diff. Default 12000.
.TP
.B --changed-only
Omit recent commits.
.TP
.B --json
Emit the axt.gitctx.v1 JSON envelope.
.TP
.B --agent
Emit minified summary-first JSONL records.
.TP
.B --print-schema [human|compact|json|agent]
Print the selected output contract and exit.
.TP
.B --list-errors
Print the standard axt error catalog as JSONL and exit.
.TP
.B --limit N
Maximum agent records.
.TP
.B --max-bytes BYTES
Maximum agent output bytes.
.TP
.B --strict
Exit non-zero if output truncation is required.
.SH EXIT STATUS
Uses the standard axt exit-code catalog. Notable codes include 0 for success,
3 for path_not_found, 6 for output_truncated_strict, 8 for io_error, and 12 for
git_unavailable.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR axt-peek (1),
.BR axt-slice (1),
.BR git-status (1),
.BR git-diff (1),
.BR git-log (1)
